text:
"Sone de yaar" 
- rathore, 2017,18,19. 
Aur Bhai Adi!! Hopefully abhi BT khatm ho gayi hogi zindagi ki kaafi had tk!! I was really happy the day I got to know youve sorted things out!! I know it had been hard for you for nearly a year but you made it through anyway!! I still remember the zumba in the orientation, when most of the people around us were not exactly interested in dancing and then there were us - OAT ke sabse last wali seedhi pe jo saath me naache the bakchodi me that was a very nice evening. I could enjoy that because of you man cause I know for sure akela toh nahi hi naachne wala tha mai kisibhi haalat me xD. Thanks for that!! I also remember that ome time you encouraged me to come to the tracks with you foe the runs and made me go for a run in the mornings too. I remember the countless times we turned the lights of our room in the night because seniors were in the wing. I remember those failed attempts at waking people up in the mornimg kust for breakfast. I remember that annoying samsung alarm which used to wake us up for the PE101 sessions. I remember the EDM nights that we attended together and had loads of fun. 
Thank you for all these memories!! All the best for your future!! Love you man!!

text:
Yo Dhawal!! 
Bhai bahot si memories judi hai yaar tumhare saath!! Regarding the night when the third yearites caught us, I too felt the same way lol!! I was shit scared what would happen and shayad mere chehre se dikh bhi rha hoga but still it was a fun night. Do know that I was looking forward to dance to rocky/disco song and certainly not a slow arijit singh song üòõ. I had spent two years of my life in kota away from my home but somehow in the initial days i was still feeling a bit homesick. This was in the very beginning of the orientation and I didn't know kaise logon se milunga and kya hoga aage. But you did a very good job on distracting me from these thoughts of homesickness and making me focus on the fun part of college life instead. I will never forget the roasts of the people( mostly tamonud and divyanshu ). Tum kaafi mazedaar insaan ho bhai!! Gaana gaa lete ho, poems likh lete ho, bakchod writing skills, mathematics strong hai, basketball khel lete jo itna bakchod, funny ho kaafi(ngl I still laugh at the story of 'kiski **** me kitne **** aaj ginega deepak **** sometimes). Thanks for all these memories!! I really cant keep a track but there are lots of memories and I thank you for that!! 
Thanks for being there bruh. I have always been admiring you and there were times when you just made me forget about the hard part of life with your hilarious joles and roasts. 
Thanks for teaching me how not to look like a creep when you're checking out girls in Antaragni üòõ!! 
I know there are some uncertainties in life as of now regarding the career choices and about persuing things that you're passionate about. But do know this - I believe in you!! I know you will do good in whateger field you choose to be in. Sure, there might have to struggke a bit in the beginning. But I know you will figure it out and bakiyo ka pata nai hai but you have my support üòÉ. All the best for your future!! Baki yaar tum Delhi me hi ho agar toh pakka milna hoga apna toh - pawri karte hai milke jaldi hi !! Love you man üíû

text:
Yo bro!! I don‚Äôt remember when did we meet for the first time. I think it was the TA lab and I thought damn saare CSE walo ko group in kar Diya hai yaha toh sare maggu log honge. But there were us!! Bunch of nerds trying to seek fun in things that were not that intereseting and boy did that turn out well. I always admired you for the level of hardwork that you put into things and I really feel it is your best quality. There is one thing however that I think you should know and it is that you are an extra ordinary person bruh. You may not believe it at times and think that you are just an ordinary guy who would not be able to do much but I know you're not. You're awesome!! Itna sab kuch karke bhi FB stories me positivity failaate ho logon me. You surely lift up spirits too!! There were times when I was not feeling good but you were there - sharing wholesome memes, laughing at the silly jokes that I used to slip in between and yet helping me out in academics at the same time. Thanks for that, thanks for existing. I cant imagine what would have been my situation in some of the courses if you were not there. I love how you also have a similar taste in music and also the feel good memes and the literature as well!! Baki bro mai tumhe kya time management sikhau tum khud itni saari cheeze manage karte ho- you are really breathtaking. I was not really a nightout wala guy in the first year. But when I met you in 4th sem and saw you just flipping the side of the match just through nights -  i was really motivated ( lmao you did a DS assignment once throughout the night and I was really awestruck. I thought ye bande ka ye assignment toh gaya time hi nai bacha hai and there were you!! Damn it was the first time I saw someone do that tbh and later on tumhare saath reh reh ke mai wo bhi sikh gaya) . I do not have much words how to thank you and I can not yet imagine what would the journey look like without you in it., Because seriously, you were there with me in the darkest semester - I remember all the nightouts and countless deadlines and the scary nights of OS. You were there all the times and you helped me get through it. Thanks a lot. Baki bro, milte hai Noida me Party karenge saath me and bakchodiya karenge aur bhi!! All the best for your future - no doubt tum chaapoge aage bhi!! Cause I believe in you and you are enough!!

text:
To,
the Based Chairperson Gang,
Vrooooooooooooooo!!!!!
You're the wisest homie out of all the homies and ngl I really got to learn a lot from you. A wise man once said "you should not call someone your best friend because then you are comparing your friends and that is not good".  Ironically, the very first line of this memoir compares you with other people but okay. you are really a very awesome person and I am grateful that I got a chance to meet you in my life. I remember we met for the first time in first year summers lol. It was the phy103 AM thingy on which we worked together. I hate that we did not get to hang out in the last month of iitk. But hey, Gurgaon aur Noida ke beech kitna hi fasla hai lol. I really like how I could easily message you regarding how the Y18 is fucked up in ESC and we should do something and how easily we went on board and actually helped them. Thanks, for everything. All the best for the future endeavours. Love you <3.

text:
Hehe bro, 
ye memoir me kya hi likhu ab samajh nai aa rha. Jab bhi kuch kehna hota hai tumse mai toh seedha keh deta hu tumhe dont think aisa kuch hoga jo nahi keh paaya hounga. Thanks for giving me that space and trusting me at the same time. I remember that one time when you sensed that I might be overthinking things and might be in the guilt that I have messed up things. You knew I might be hurting myself just by overthinking on that and you sent me the most comforting text one could possibly send at that time. tbh I was really really scared at that time and you helped me. Life is weird no? Sometimes we help people and we think that it is a very small thing for us but it really means a lot to them. Thanks for that. Well this was just one incident, I think there a lot more incidents where you helped me when I wasn't doing okay, Even lockdown ke time me you were one of the very few people jinse meri har roz baat hoti thi and I think uska reason bhi obvious hai. You end up where you find most comfortable.  Thanks for existing. Thanks for everything. I will never forget the antaragni nights when we scrolled tinder together, the nights in sixth semester when we bonded and opened up to each other, that one whole night when we shared the gossips, the days when we planned out things together, the last night when you gave me that letter and other countless occasions. It was a very wonderful journey. A journey holistic journey in fact. I really enjoyed the journey and I hope you enjoyed it too!! Thanks for making it special. You are one of the few people I go to whenever I do not feel good and yet everytime you make me feel great about myself. Thanks for existing. I really hope we get to meet soon and complete all the pending pawris. All the best!! Also, I believe in you, no matter what other people say - I know you are a wonderful person and you  will achieve great things in life. Congratulations future Yashika for all the success!! Love you!!
